    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Yordan Alvarez** (70.94) and **Junior Caminero** (69.34) anchor the Zurich Zebras lineup as our strongest plays. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a steady matchup against Will Warren, where a combination of a favorable batting order (#2) and a strong xwOBA profile drives his elite score. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** finds himself in a prime spot against Taj Bradley, bolstered by an 11% skill-based boost against the opposing pitcher that outweighs his slight park-factor penalty. While **Trea Turner** (68.42) remains a high-floor engine atop the order against Grant Holmes, the strategic weight we place on stolen base efficiency ensures that **Caleb Durbin** (67.42) remains a core start despite his lower-order placement; his 16% SP skill advantage and high park factor make him a critical asset for our scarcity-driven roster strategy.\n\nThe decision to keep **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.22) on the bench was the most difficult call of the morning. While he projects as a high-upside play, he ultimately missed the cut due to a tough matchup against Emmet Sheehan, whose 3.20 xERA stifled his base projection significantly more than the mid-tier options currently starting. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Caleb Durbin**, as his 67.42 score carries a 34% rain risk warning that could force a late-game pivot to a reserve like **Carson Benge** (48.47) if the game is delayed or postponed. While **Dillon Dingler** (61.29) is a strong play thanks to a massive 14% platoon edge against Andrew Abbott, we are cautious about relying on any \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions; if **Dillon Dingler** or **Colt Keith** (#3, 53.45) fall out of their anticipated slots, we will re-evaluate our bench depth to ensure we maximize our daily game caps without sacrificing our core speed categories.",
